cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.SD (Sound) sub-category as it deals with speech recognition systems and waveforms. It could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it involves natural language processing. The use of deep learning suggests it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Signal Processing) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on improving performance suggests it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
